</head>

<portpage logo="50.gif" logowidth="124" logoheight="85">
  <portabout>
   <para>
      NetBSD/sun2 is the port of NetBSD to the <ulink
      url="http://www.sun.com/">Sun Microsystems</ulink> <emphasis
      role="bold">sun2</emphasis> series of computers, which are based
      on the Motorola 68010 CPU with a Sun-designed custom MMU. Sun
      sold these computers as both servers and desktop workstations
      from the early to mid 1980's. They were superseded by the
      <emphasis role="bold">sun3</emphasis> systems, which are
      supported by NetBSD as NetBSD/sun3.
   </para>

   <para>
     Matt Fredette is the maintainer of NetBSD/sun2.
   </para>
  </portabout>

